short.am,ar,bg,bn,ca,cs,da,de,el,en,en_AU,en_G: Save pages and remind you to come back and look at them.

long.am,ar,bg,bn,ca,cs,da,de,el,en,en_AU,en_G:
# 0.1.7 [✨New✨]
- You can now name folders to get a quick overview of their contents.

# 0.1.6 [✨New✨]
- Now supports opening all pages saved from one window in a newly opened window.

# 0.1.5
- Now supports deleting all pages from one window with only two clicks.

# 0.1.4
- Set timepicker's default time to 1 hour from now.

# 0.1.3
- Collapse all groups by default.

When we browse around on the web, we often open a lot of tabs and just won't close them. Sometimes it's because the work or reading on the pages is not finished yet. This extension helps you save current tab or current window, to get back to them later. You can set reminders on the saved pages, and you'll get a reminder in time.

Thanks for using Look Back. If you have any questions or suggestions, please leave a comment.
